    "synopsis": "Inquisitor Rostov's hunt for the Hand of Abaddon finally turns up the intelligence he has been chasing across the crusade, and he calls in every blade he can still trust. On the Anaxian Line, Ultramarines Lieutenant Ferren Areios stumbles into a dread vision that ties him to an old comrade's path. Magda Kesh marches with the 84th Mordian, refusing the destiny pressed onto her by the men and miracles that surround her. And inside the shifting court of the Archenemy, the acolyte Tharador Yheng strains to slip free of her master Tenebrus's shadow, while the Red Corsair Graeyl Herek chases his own claim on the Dark Gods' favour. Both want the same ancient evil - and whichever one of them takes it will reshape the war between the Imperium and Chaos.",
